{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "intersectionstitch", "icon": "SOP/intersectionstitch", "tags": "points, polygons, curves, intersections, stitch, analysis", "since": "16.0", "verb_since": "16.5", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Intersection Stitch"], "extent": [0, 24]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Composes triangle surfaces and curves together into a single connected mesh."], "extent": [208, 292]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This low-level node can be used to build higher-level tools dealing with intersecting geometry, such as the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/boolean", "type": "link", "text": ["Boolean node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/boolean"}, ". If you just want to merge polygonal geometry, use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/boolean", "type": "link", "text": ["Boolean"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/boolean"}, "."], "extent": [292, 513]}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [513, 521], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Connect a triangle mesh to the first input and a curve mesh to the second input (or the reverse). This node composes the inputs together into a single connected mesh."], "extent": [521, 690]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If you don\u2019t connect the third input, the node uses the functionality from ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/intersectionanalysis", "type": "link", "text": ["Intersection Analysis"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/intersectionanalysis"}, " to automatically find intersections in the meshes."], "extent": [690, 871]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Optionally, you can connect the third input with point geometry with attributes as created by ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/intersectionanalysis", "type": "link", "text": ["Intersection Analysis"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/intersectionanalysis"}, " or the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/scatter", "type": "link", "text": ["Scatter node"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/scatter"}, ". This lets you edit the intersection points before using them to connect the meshes."], "extent": [871, 1145]}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1145, 1157], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group A"], "extent": [1157, 1167], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A list of primitives to check from the first input. If this is blank, the node checks all primitives."], "extent": [1167, 1274]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Group B"], "extent": [1274, 1283], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["A list of primitives to check from the second input. If this is blank, the node checks all primitives."], "extent": [1283, 1391]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Proximity Tolerance"], "extent": [1391, 1412], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["How close points have to be (in Houdini units) for the node to connect them."], "extent": [1412, 1494]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Split Curves"], "extent": [1494, 1508], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["???"], "extent": [1508, 1518]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1518, 1527], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/intersectionanalysis", "type": "link", "text": "", "ful